@node "Registration" "Registration"
WarpDTPrefs is part of the WarpDT package, and is SHAREWARE, which
means you are expected to register if you find it useful, and wish to
continue using it.  I have decided not to cripple the datatype at all
during the evaluation period, so everybody can judge for themselves if this
product is worth buying.

Registration of the WarpDT package costs È15 (GBP), entitling you to
unlimited usage of all the WarpDTs for all CPU/OS versions. At this time,
this one-time registration fee entitles you to full versions of any new
datatypes added to the WarpDT family in the future.

To register, please visit http://www.warpdt.co.uk/ for further
instructions.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"
To install WarpDTPrefs, simply run the provided installer script by
double-clicking the icon.

Alternatively, just drag the WarpDT icon to a location of your choice (e.g.
SYS:Prefs).
@endnode

@node "Acknowledgements" "Acknowledgements"
The ATO (Amiga Translators Organization - http://ato.vapor.com) handled the
localization of the program strings, installer and documentation.  Thanks to
everyone who was involved in translating to various languages.

Thanks to H&P and the OS 3.5 development team, especially for the brilliant
ReActor, which I use to create/manage the GUI for this program.
@endnode

@node "Future" "Support & the Future"
If you have any suggestions, please @{"let me know" link "Author" 0}.

Future releases of WarpDTPrefs will be available from either Aminet
(util/dtype/WarpDTPrefs.lha) or its webpage:

  http://www.warpdt.co.uk/prefs.html

If you would you like to know when WarpDTPrefs is next updated, then you
may want to subscribe to my announcement list to receive an e-mail
informing you of the changes as soon as a new versions of any of my
products are released.  To subscribe, send a blank e-mail to

  futaura-announce-subscribe@yahoogroups.com

or go to

  http://groups.yahoo.com/subscribe/futaura-announce
@endnode

